623	108	\N	2	SuccessStoryDetailComponent	"body"=>"<p><em>This article first appeared on</em><em> the Shopper Technology Institute.</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>January 24, 2012</strong> <strong>&ndash;</strong>&nbsp;The exhibit hall at last week&rsquo;s National Retail Federation 101st Annual&nbsp;Convention in New York was full of new cutting-edge applications for attendees to evaluate. The atmosphere was electric with positive vibes from buyers and sellers for the new year.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNRF billed the event&rsquo;s theme as Retail&rsquo;s New Rules. This was manifested in many ways, but two stood out: one was an on-site survey of attendees, and the other was a presentation of new merchandising strategies for retail growth.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\"http://www.maxpoint.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Maxpoint</a>, a firm that helps retailers and brands drive in-store traffic with technology that delivers scalable neighborhood-level online campaigns, accumulated&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://maxpoint.com/us/advertising-tips-and-strategies/advertising-insights/101-rules\\" target=\\"_blank\\">101 New Rules for Retail</a>&nbsp;by surveying retailers, technology vendors and consultants on the show floor.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere were four common themes:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Mobile Adoption</strong><br />\r\nWhether it was launching a mobile shopping app or enabling mobile payments, attendees placed great emphasis on the need for a mobile strategy in 2012.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Creating a Seamless Cross-Channel Customer Experience</strong><br />\r\nAttendees recognized the continued need to provide a seamless cross-channel experience. One attendee commented, &ldquo;It shouldn&rsquo;t matter what channel my customer comes in through or whether they use multiple channels before ultimately making their purchase. They should receive the same experience at every touch point.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Security </strong><br />\r\nFrom PCI compliance to securing customer information, security is a top priority for many show attendees this year.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Customer Service </strong><br />\r\nA number of respondents shared that they will be placing more emphasis on better customer service and satisfying the customer at every interaction in 2012 because &ldquo;people remember good service.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Our survey revealed that retailers and the vendors that serve them have reverted back to the very first rule of retail &ndash; put the customer first. Many of the rules attendees shared &ndash; whether it was the enablement of mobile payments or focusing on regional relevance &ndash; came back to creating the best possible experience for the consumer,&rdquo; commented MaxPoint&rsquo;s Vice President of Marketing Lynn Vitello.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAmong the 101 new rules were several that dealt with shopper technology: Use mobile to drive customers to the store; learn the skills necessary to use social media channels effectively; use different types of in-store media &ndash; retail soundtrack, digital signage, even the scent of the store should be a focus; implement mobile self-checkout that is integrated with analytics so we have a better view into our in-store shoppers; use mobile for loyalty programs and don&rsquo;t require customers to carry loyalty cards; merge customer loyalty with mobile location and CRM; create a single view of all our data &ndash; POS, loyalty, etc.; innovate around mobile and radio frequency management; and others.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a special seminar, Craig Riner, Vice President of Marketing for Rite-Aid Corp., and Michelle Klingensmith, Shopper Marketing Manager with Glaxo-SmithKline Consumer Healthcare, presented six merchandising strategies for retail growth:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Be relevant, personal and solution oriented. Rite-Aid customizes its shopper offering through its wellness+ loyalty program.</li>\r\n\t<li>Create a digital habit for traditionally off-line behavior. Rite-Aid shoppers can earn discounts by watching informational videos. Another program lets shoppers look for coupons by brand, category or value to be loaded to their loyalty card.</li>\r\n\t<li>Advanced planning makes a difference. Manufacturers and vendors need to understand the retailers&rsquo; long-term strategy and help them succeed.</li>\r\n\t<li>Combine content with value. Use videos to communicate content, product and price.</li>\r\n\t<li>Rely on data and adjust strategies. Analysis of data provides new learning that leads to better strategies.</li>\r\n\t<li>Use customers as a source of strategic advantage. Listen to shoppers and learn.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n", "title"=>"New Rules of Retail Set Tone for 2012 ", "sidebar_text"=>"", "sidebar_image_uid"=>NULL, "sidebar_image_name"=>NULL, "sidebar_image_link_target"=>"_blank", "sidebar_image_link_page_id"=>"-1", "sidebar_image_link_external_url"=>"http://www.shoppertech.org/"	\N	2013-05-15 00:26:31.539067	2013-08-27 20:33:26.282732
