696	131	\N	3	SuccessStoryDetailComponent	"body"=>"<p><strong>MaxPoint Interactive hit the show</strong> floor at the National Retail Federation (NRF) 101st Annual Convention &amp; Expo to get a pulse on what&rsquo;s hot in 2012. The company surveyed 101 show attendees, asking &ldquo;What is your new rule for retail in 2012?&rdquo; Here&rsquo;s what they shared with us:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Use mobile to drive customers to the store</li>\r\n\t<li>Empower district and regional managers</li>\r\n\t<li>Use mobile to create a seamless experience &ndash; use any/all screens</li>\r\n\t<li>Step up our Web strategy to better compete against Amazon</li>\r\n\t<li>Get product into customers&rsquo; hands &ndash; regardless of where they find it, they want it &ndash; so ship it to them!</li>\r\n\t<li>Learn the skills necessary to use social media channels effectively&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li>Create a seamless cross-channel experience</li>\r\n\t<li>Get rid of clunky cash registers and implement mobile POS</li>\r\n\t<li>Extend touch points to more channels &ndash; give customers the opportunity to interact with us on their terms</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus on integrated loss prevention</li>\r\n\t<li>Protect customer information &ndash; go beyond PCI compliance</li>\r\n\t<li>Evaluate emerging payments &ndash; anything non-card based will be big in 2012</li>\r\n\t<li>It all fails in execution, so we&rsquo;ll be spending more time thinking through our store operations before implementing anything</li>\r\n\t<li>Work towards a seamless multichannel experience</li>\r\n\t<li>Invest in the cloud &ndash; cheaper, less support</li>\r\n\t<li>Integrate back-end inventory to be able to create better promotional opportunities</li>\r\n\t<li>Create a compelling experience &ndash; how they get there is irrelevant, it&rsquo;s about the experience when the customer gets there</li>\r\n\t<li>Use different types of in-store media &ndash; retail soundtrack, digital signage, even the scent of the store should be a focus</li>\r\n\t<li>PCI compliance</li>\r\n\t<li>More training for store associates</li>\r\n\t<li>Create a better customer experience across channels &ndash; &ldquo;click-and-mortar&rdquo;</li>\r\n\t<li>Implement mobile self-checkout that is integrated with analytics so we have a better view into our in-store shoppers</li>\r\n\t<li>Keep focused on customer service</li>\r\n\t<li>Do not underestimate the impact of Amazon</li>\r\n\t<li>Watch the price</li>\r\n\t<li>It&rsquo;s all about the customer experience and learning how to harness social media frenzies.&nbsp; We also focused on how to attract a new generation &ndash; their needs are so different</li>\r\n\t<li>Be positioned for change &ndash; technology is changing the way retailers reach consumers and, as retailers, we need to be ready to reach them everywhere</li>\r\n\t<li>Use mobile for loyalty programs; don&rsquo;t require customers to carry loyalty cards</li>\r\n\t<li>Evaluate mobile payments</li>\r\n\t<li>Develop good products &ndash; don&rsquo;t get caught up in trends; stick to your core business</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus on good service; people will remember good service</li>\r\n\t<li>Enable our customers to scan everything in the store with their mobile and checkout from their phone</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus on regional relevance &ndash; localize the experience and the assortment</li>\r\n\t<li>Secure transactions across all channels; any retailer with an Internet connection should be concerned with security</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus more on managing our customer base through effective loyalty programs</li>\r\n\t<li>Global supply chain optimization and managing flow of goods</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve store communications from HQ to regional and store managers</li>\r\n\t<li>Convergence of payment transactions and applications on one circuit in the cloud</li>\r\n\t<li>Satisfy the customer at every interaction</li>\r\n\t<li>Mobility &ndash; enable in-store scanning of products</li>\r\n\t<li>Be smarter &ndash; know who your customer is and what they want the minute they walk in the store</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve the customer experience. Then improve it some more</li>\r\n\t<li>Customer centricity through multi-channel profiling</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve the shopper experience while reducing labor costs for better ROI</li>\r\n\t<li>Automate cash handling</li>\r\n\t<li>Merge customer loyalty with mobile location and CRM</li>\r\n\t<li>Make the self-checkout screen the same as the ones store associates are using so they can better help customers through the self-checkout process without having to be trained on multiple systems</li>\r\n\t<li>PCI compliance &ndash; network security</li>\r\n\t<li>Multichannel marketing &ndash; social media, mobile, kiosks</li>\r\n\t<li>Figure out our tablet strategy &ndash; both for shoppers and for store associates</li>\r\n\t<li>Invest in software that scales</li>\r\n\t<li>Safety and security in mobile transactions</li>\r\n\t<li>Better customer experiences on devices</li>\r\n\t<li>Spend less on frivolous promotions this year, such as sports sponsorships</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve the bottom line by cutting POP waste</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus on the mobile consumer</li>\r\n\t<li>Listen to conversations customers are having about our brand on social networks</li>\r\n\t<li>Launch a mobile app</li>\r\n\t<li>Look within and improve our employee benefits and perks</li>\r\n\t<li>Remember the customer is #1</li>\r\n\t<li>Better engagement on our site to keep customers on our site longer</li>\r\n\t<li>More directivity and self-engagement</li>\r\n\t<li>Manage discounts more effectively</li>\r\n\t<li>Put an emphasis on mobile shopping</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus on consumer retention</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve our staffing to store traffic ratio</li>\r\n\t<li>Security in payment processing</li>\r\n\t<li>We&rsquo;ll be focusing our energy on loss prevention</li>\r\n\t<li>Find new ways to improve margins</li>\r\n\t<li>Become more innovative with more advanced technology</li>\r\n\t<li>Put the customer first</li>\r\n\t<li>Teach store/regional managers about the technology we&rsquo;ve invested in so they can use it to better engage at the store-level</li>\r\n\t<li>Invest in mobile POS</li>\r\n\t<li>Minimize POP waste</li>\r\n\t<li>Mobility will be a big focus this year</li>\r\n\t<li>Take a structured approach to visual technology and art</li>\r\n\t<li>7Support our customer service teams with better technology so they are more productive</li>\r\n\t<li>Stop shrinkage</li>\r\n\t<li>Create a single view of all our data &ndash; POS, loyalty, etc.</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve the in-store experience by integrating shopper technology</li>\r\n\t<li>Focus more on my customers and work to constantly improve their experience</li>\r\n\t<li>Remote device management</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve customer service</li>\r\n\t<li>Figure out how to use mobile &ndash; both in the store and to drive people to nearest locations</li>\r\n\t<li>Multichannel management &ndash; create a seamless connection between channels</li>\r\n\t<li>Figure out a way to convert more of our online browsers to buyers</li>\r\n\t<li>Increase online engagement</li>\r\n\t<li>Expand upon applications for prepaid cards</li>\r\n\t<li>Get our online business up and running</li>\r\n\t<li>Roll out in-store pickup for our online orders</li>\r\n\t<li>Improve our supply chain to become more efficient</li>\r\n\t<li>Diversify to new markets</li>\r\n\t<li>Make sure mobile retail transactions are secure</li>\r\n\t<li>Better understand our customers&rsquo; needs and wants</li>\r\n\t<li>Innovate around mobile and radio frequency management</li>\r\n\t<li>Maximize our floor space in each location</li>\r\n\t<li>Create new consumer packaging using 3D technology</li>\r\n\t<li>Automate technology to increase customer share</li>\r\n\t<li>Greater penetration in wireless PCI scanning</li>\r\n\t<li>Roll out mobile solutions</li>\r\n\t<li>The rule is &ldquo;There is no rule. I don&rsquo;t want to restrict myself to what I can do this year.&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n", "title"=>"101 New Rules for Retail", "sidebar_text"=>"", "header_image_uid"=>NULL, "header_image_name"=>NULL, "sidebar_image_link_target"=>"", "sidebar_image_link_page_id"=>"", "sidebar_image_link_external_url"=>""	\N	2013-05-15 06:42:28.102806	2013-07-08 13:42:18.147902
