1612	190	\N	2	SuccessStoryDetailComponent	"body"=>"<p><strong>Durham, N.C.&nbsp;&ndash;</strong> <strong>December 11, 2013</strong> <strong>&ndash;</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://www.johnavery.org\\" target=\\"_blank\\">John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club of Durham</a> today announced that Morrisville-based <a href=\\"http://www.maxpoint.com\\" target=\\"_blank\\">MaxPoint</a>, the company that helps retailers and brands drive in-store sales with its innovative Digital Zip<sup>&reg;</sup> technology, is the sole local sponsor of the organization&rsquo;s <a href=\\"http://www.bgca.org/ClubTech/Pages/index.aspx\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Club Tech</a>. The unique program provides young children with the guidance, skills and resources needed to succeed in school and, eventually, the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The national program is made possible at the local level by MaxPoint, which provided a donation to support purchases of equipment, field trips and teacher salaries. In addition, MaxPoint &ndash; the 9th fastest growing company in North America on Deloitte&rsquo;s Technology Fast 500&trade; &ndash; donated the costs and time associated with nearly 50 volunteers participating in technology career training and mentoring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Club Tech enriches Durham youth by teaching teamwork, responsibility and components of STEM (science, technology, engineering and math). The program also assists with potential career choices and implements appropriate technological curriculums by arranging guest speakers, mentor programs, field trips and comprehensive surveys to understand students&rsquo; goals and abilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to its support of Club Tech, MaxPoint created the &ldquo;Design on a Dime&rdquo; event for its employees this holiday season. The event involves redesigning and redecorating the John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club, as well as providing various technological updates throughout the facility. Since October, MaxPoint employees have worked to create redesign plans for the club spaces and will divide into teams on December 12 to enhance d&eacute;cor and technology capabilities throughout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Our club has chosen STEM as a core program focus for 2014,&rdquo; said Jerome Levisy, CEO of John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club. &ldquo;MaxPoint is a premier technology company that embraces positive community programs. Technology is rapidly advancing, and MaxPoint&rsquo;s efforts allow us to educate our youth and prepare them for future success. We are honored to call ourselves a partner.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Each year, our company is proud to support and work alongside the great people at John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club,&rdquo; said Joe Epperson, CEO of MaxPoint. &ldquo;We are grateful to be part of such a vibrant, talented community. Volunteering our time with the Boys &amp; Girls Club is our way of giving back while also helping to create the next generation of the Triangle&rsquo;s tech community.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club, a private, nonprofit organization dedicated to educating and protecting children while preserving the beauty and innocence of childhood, serves more than 700 children every year, making a difference in the lives of all youth, but especially those who need guidance the most.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information about John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club, visit <a href=\\"http://www.johnavery.org\\" target=\\"_blank\\">www.johnavery.org</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To learn more about Club Tech, visit <a href=\\"http://www.bgca.org/ClubTech/Pages/index.aspx\\" target=\\"_blank\\">www.bgca.org/ClubTech</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About John Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club of Durham</strong><br />\r\nJohn Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club is an IRS recognized 501(c)(3) organization. Chartered in 1939, the club serves over 700 children annually, age 6&ndash;18, in programs centered on character and leadership, academics, fine arts, sports, fitness and healthy lifestyles. For more information, visit <a href=\\"http://www.johnavery.org\\" target=\\"_blank\\">www.johnavery.org</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About MaxPoint </strong><br />\r\nMaxPoint uses hyperlocal intelligence to help retailers, brands, and agencies make smarter digital advertising decisions. The company&rsquo;s Digital Zip<sup>&reg;</sup> technology employs the latest in machine learning to pinpoint the neighborhoods of consumers most likely to purchase an advertiser&rsquo;s products and services at local stores. Trusted by 13 of the 15 most advertised US brands and all of the top US media agencies, MaxPoint is the only solution of its kind to offer hyperlocal precision at scale. For more information, visit <a href=\\"http://www.maxpoint.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">www.maxpoint.com</a>, follow MaxPoint on Twitter <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/#!/maxpoint_int\\" target=\\"_blank\\">@maxpoint_int</a>, and subscribe to the <a href=\\"http://maxpoint.com/onpoint-blog/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">OnPoint Blog</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Contact:</strong><br />\r\nJerome Levisy<br />\r\nJohn Avery Boys &amp; Girls Club of Durham<br />\r\n919-687-4517<br />\r\n<a href=\\"mailto:jlevisy@johnavery.org\\">jlevisy@johnavery.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Katie Sullivan<br />\r\nfama PR<br />\r\n617-986-5031&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<a href=\\"mailto:maxpoint@famapr.com\\">maxpoint@famapr.com</a></p>\r\n", "title"=>"John Avery Boys & Girls Club of Durham Partners with MaxPoint for Local Career Guidance and Club Tech Program", "sidebar_text"=>"", "sidebar_image_link_target"=>"", "sidebar_image_link_page_id"=>"", "sidebar_image_link_external_url"=>""	\N	2013-12-11 15:39:26.518478	2013-12-11 16:27:27.517606
