581	88	\N	2	SuccessStoryDetailComponent	"body"=>"<p><em>This article first appeared on CMO.COM.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 15, 2012</strong>&nbsp;<strong>&ndash;</strong> In a new research report sponsored by MaxPoint, BIGinsight reveals the changing behavior among today&rsquo;s cost-conscious grocery shoppers as they move through the path to purchase. The Grocery Industry Pulse titled, &ldquo;Reaching Today&rsquo;s Cost-Conscious Consumer,&rdquo; reveals that the average monthly spend on groceries has steadily increased among the general population from pre- to post-recession. While spending continues to climb, nearly three in four respondents have made changes to their grocery shopping habits within the last year, becoming more cost-conscious before and during their trips.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\"http://offers.maxpoint.com/GroceryShopperInsights.html\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Download</a>&nbsp;the free report!</p>\r\n", "title"=>"Grocery Industry Pulse: Reaching Today’s Cost-Conscious Consumer", "sidebar_text"=>"", "sidebar_image_uid"=>NULL, "sidebar_image_name"=>NULL, "sidebar_image_link_target"=>"_blank", "sidebar_image_link_page_id"=>"-1", "sidebar_image_link_external_url"=>"http://cmo.com/"	\N	2013-05-15 00:00:48.484714	2013-09-25 15:21:02.45891
