661	1	15	dont-overlook-emerging-audiences-in-your-advertising-strategy	Don't Overlook Emerging Audiences in Your Advertising Strategy	<p>My husband is a stay at home dad and about a decade ago, it was an extremely rare role for a male to play.&nbsp; Today, it is much more common; to the tune of 158,000 stay at home dads in the US according to the US Census Bureau.&nbsp; This number is expected to grow significantly over the next 5 years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>My husband is a stay at home dad and about a decade ago, it was an extremely rare role for a male to play.&nbsp; Today, it is much more common; to the tune of 158,000 stay at home dads in the US according to the US Census Bureau.&nbsp; This number is expected to grow significantly over the next 5 years.&nbsp; <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can see how many active stay at home dads are out there through a simple browser search or typing &ldquo;SAHD&rdquo; (stay at home dad acronym) in the Twitter search.&nbsp; It is a very real and lucrative market that would be considered an emerging or growing market for retailers.&nbsp; Such a market should not be overlooked, but rather studied for what appeals to a stay at home dad.&nbsp; The psychology will certainly be different from that of a stay at home mom.&nbsp; Making the mistake of using the same marketing strategy for both could prove to be catastrophic to your marketing efforts and campaigns.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOne of the first retailers to specifically target stay at home dads is Kellogg&rsquo;s.&nbsp; According to an Ad Age article <a href="http://adage.com/article/news/kellogg-s-tony-tiger-60-changing-a-age/229493/" target="_blank">A Tiger at 60: How Kellogg&#39;s Tony Is Changing for a New Age: Frosted Flakes Mascot Being Used in Push Toward Dads</a>, Frosted Flakes is reaching out to fathers with TV ads that show a dad, son and Tony tossing a football in the backyard. The trio then heads to the kitchen for some post-game Flakes, as the voiceover intones &quot;