659	1	15	making-the-most-out-of-data-a-look-back-into-the-walmart-nielsen-partnership	Making the Most Out of Data: A Look Back Into the Walmart-Nielsen Partnership	<p>This past July, Walmart made the decision (after a ten year break) to share sales data with third-party firms, leading to Walmart&rsquo;s widely talked about partnership with Nielsen. This data includes food, consumables and health and wellness categories, and was a huge step forward for not only Walmart but the industry in general.</p>\r\n	<p>This past July, Walmart made the decision (after a ten year break) to share sales data with third-party firms, leading to Walmart&rsquo;s widely talked about partnership with Nielsen. This data includes food, consumables and health and wellness categories, and was a huge step forward for not only Walmart but the industry in general. <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://risnews.edgl.com/retail-news%5CWalmart-Nielsen-Data-Sharing-Deal-Fills-Long-Standing-Analytical-Gap74469" target="_blank">This news</a> continues to be a hot topic because Walmart accounts for one-third to one-half of a consumer product&rsquo;s market share &ndash; truly, the world&rsquo;s largest retailer. Accounting for a large chunk of average household spending, this data gives the retail and CPG industry more insight into consumer demand patterns.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to Walter Simon, CEO of Walmart, sharing this information helps optimize the business, enabling store operators to react and quickly make changes in their local stores. Like many others, Simon realized the potential for data analysis and how it can impact a company&rsquo;s ability to identify category opportunities and work with suppliers to develop customer-driving programs. And, based on Q2 sales, Walmart has confirmed that this was the right decision to make.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe proper analysis, combined with the right data can truly make a difference in sales when it comes to effectively leveraging campai