671	1	15	rei-goes-local-with-social-media-strategy-2	REI Goes Local with Social Media Strategy	<p>REI (Recreational Equipment Incorporated) makes a national brand feel local with such ease that it&rsquo;s easy to take for granted. Each of their just less than 120 stores is staffed with expert outdoor enthusiasts.&nbsp; In addition to being a retailer, they have become advisors for consumers considering purchases of outdoor equipment. It&rsquo;s one of their biggest strengths as a brand and it&rsquo;s also why I choose to shop with them. &nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>REI (Recreational Equipment Incorporated) makes a national brand feel local with such ease that it&rsquo;s easy to take for granted. Each of their just less than 120 stores is staffed with expert outdoor enthusiasts.&nbsp; In addition to being a retailer, they have become advisors for consumers considering purchases of outdoor equipment. It&rsquo;s one of their biggest strengths as a brand and it&rsquo;s also why I choose to shop with them. &nbsp;<!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nJust the other day I visited a neighborhood REI store to try out a mountain bike. Not only was the person assisting me an avid cyclist, she knew the trails in my area I intend to ride, and she was a &ldquo;she&rdquo; - perfect for recommending a women&rsquo;s bike. The experience was personal: tailored to me, my needs, my budget and my particular location. In the end, I felt confident and excited about my purchasing decision. The experience was everything that Lynn didn&rsquo;t get out of her visit to the <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2011/10/7/poor-customer-service-can-undo-retailers-efforts-to-drive-in-store-sales-2" target="_blank">local tennis shop</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis excellent in-store service gives REI quite a bit to live up to when it comes to their social media strategy. When REI rolled out their regional twitter strategy recently, I realized that they had clearly hit the nail on the 