696	1	15	digital-advertising-and-pre-store-planning-a-likely-pair	Digital Advertising and Pre-Store Planning: A Likely Pair	<p>Most consumers prepare a list before shopping - it is rarely a spontaneous event. For many, much thought and planning goes into preparing for every shopping trip. Even though the shopper ends up making the purchase in the store, the decision making begins online &ndash; cue digital advertising.</p>\r\n	<p>Most consumers prepare a list before shopping - it is rarely a spontaneous event. For many, much thought and planning goes into preparing for every shopping trip. Nowadays, the path to purchase starts online with shoppers beginning their purchasing experience by completing online research to compare prices, quality and reviews from other shoppers. Even though the shopper ends up making the purchase in the store, the decision making begins online &ndash; cue digital advertising. <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nConsumers most often have a specific retailer/brand location in mind before heading out on a shopping trip. If a product or category from that retailer/brand is not on the list, consumers do not venture to those locations. The logical venue to turn to is online advertising where organizations can reach these consumers and target them with more accuracy. Don&rsquo;t let shoppers simply rely on web browsing to make their decisions. They are already there doing the research, so give them a digital ad to help drive them in-store.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTargeted digital campaigns result in a more engaging and relevant experience for consumers. For example, digital advertising has had significant impact for CPG brand sales. According to a <a href="http://www.comscore.com/" target="_blank">comScore</a> study, 70% of online display ad campaigns generated double-digit sales lifts, and 40% of online display ad campaigns generated sales lifts of 30% or more for brands. It&rsquo;s the continuing exposure to campaigns where consumers already spend time 