708	1	15	2012-online-advertising-and-tablets	2012, Online Advertising and Tablets	<p>In 2011, the theme of the Consumer Electronics Show was &lsquo;The Year of the Tablet,&rsquo; and more than 80 were introduced at the show. Recognizing its sleek format and technology advancements in general, the show started to generate buzz that made people sure 2011 was in fact, &lsquo;The Year of the Tablet.&rdquo;</p>\r\n	<p>In 2011, the theme of the Consumer Electronics Show was &lsquo;The Year of the Tablet,&rsquo; and more than 80 were introduced at the show. Recognizing its sleek format and technology advancements in general, the show started to generate buzz that made people sure 2011 was in fact, &lsquo;The Year of the Tablet.&rdquo;<!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd it was&hellip;with unbelievably high demand for tablets from consumers, along with the launch of multiple tablet types from different brands. However, it was not until later in 2011 where companies and advertisers, not consumers, started seeing the benefits of the tablet in its value for reaching and engaging with target audiences, getting ready for a big 2012. Below are a few reasons why.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>High adoption rates:</strong> <a href="http://www.forrester.com/rb/research/" target="_blank">Forrester</a> estimates that the current &ldquo;single digit penetration&rdquo; of tablets will increase 3-to-4 times by 2015 and with it, maturation of its usage expected. It is valued across all consumer groups, with Hispanics and Asian-Americans leading as the early adopters of the tablets. According to a recent<a href="http://www.emarketer.com/" target="_blank"> eMarketer</a> report, Hispanics and Asian-Americans are very eager to close the technologically gap, which is a great opportunity for retailers and brands to reach these shopper groups digitally.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Redefining the path-to-purchase:</strong> In a recent <a href="http://www.retailwire.com/discussion/15720/braintrust-query-how-tablets-could-revolutionize-the-shopper-path-to-purchase" target="_blank">report</a> by Retail Wire, analysts stated, &ldquo;the tablet is the first device that can actually travel with the shopper through the complete path to purchase.&rdquo;&nbsp; Inherently a mobile device, shoppers being the path to purchase by researching for coupons and other items to pick up in-store. Meanwhile, advertisers can begin to reach these shoppers online by advertising on the tablet.&nbsp; In a recent report by RetailWire, analysts say the tablet then continues to travel the path as shoppers may take it en-route with tablet shopping lists and some applications even assist shoppers during their shopping trip based on their preferences/list.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Valuable in-store assistance:</strong> More and more stores are adopting digital technologies in-store to attract and engage shoppers, tablets included. Recently, stores have been equipping employees with tablets to research any shopper questions, provide shoppers with scannable coupons at check-out and/or add elements to digital displays.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAgree? Disagree? Share your insights on Twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/maxpoint_int" target="_blank">@maxpoint_int</a> using the #2012advertising hashtag.</p>\r\n	t	2012-01-16 15:51:45	\N	2012-01-16 15:51:45	2013-10-02 14:09:22.863673	50	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, tablet, online advertising, mobile, 2012, Consumer Electronics Show, eMarketer, Forrester, RetailWire, consumers, path-to-purchase, @maxpoint_int
896	1	20	successful-multicultural-marketing-must-understand-more-than-just-country-of-origin	Successful Multicultural Marketing Must Understand More Than Just Country of Origin 	<p>For years, many American retailers and suppliers have characterized the Hispanic market in the United States as a niche market.&nbsp; However, now with the rapid multicultural growth in the U.S., the reality is that the multicultural market is now the general market.&nbsp; Reaching these markets must have meaning beyond where they came from.</p>\r\n	<p>For years, many American retailers and suppliers have characterized the Hispanic market in the United States as a niche market.&nbsp; However, now with the rapid multicultural growth in the U.S., the reality is that the multicultural market is now the general market.&nbsp; Reaching these markets must have meaning beyond where they came from.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to Walmart&#39;s director of multicultural marketing, Carla Giovannetti Dodds, &ldquo;Multicultural marketing has never been more complex than it is now. Yet, at the same time, it&#39;s never been more critical for marketers to break the code.&rdquo;&nbsp; Dodd also added, &ldquo;This is the time to make sure multicultural is at the forefront of everything we do.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDefining &quot;Hispanic&quot; or any other multicultural demographic must go beyond language, country of origin and even DMA.&nbsp; It must also include a way of life&mdash;socially and economically as well as a mental connection with each targeted area.&nbsp; In other words, connect with interests and way of life.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSoledad O&#39;Brien, acclaimed special investigations correspondent for CNN &mdash; whose mother is African-American and Cuban, and father is Australian and Irish &mdash; said there&#39;s a tendency to want to cast a wide net around a specific group of people, such as Hispanics. &quot;Where we go wrong is aiming at stereotypes instead of reality,&quot; she noted.&nbsp; &quot;If you&#39;re looking for solutions, it&#39;s a community question,&quot; she said, stressing that authenticity comes only from truly understanding the community one is trying to reach.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor example, supermarket chain Food Lion performed market surveys and a lot of data analysis to develop a Hispanic program for its stores. The program, which started as a five-store pilot in the Raleigh-Durham, N.C., area, has since been expanded to 63 stores, according to the grocer&#39;s Hispanic marketing manager, Daniel Herrara.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHispanic-specific programs are a must, he said, because &quot;when you try to translate general market programs to the Hispanic market, you are viewed as non-Hispanic.&quot; For Salisbury, N.C.-based Food Lion, a division of the Delhaize Group, loyalty rewards programs tailored specifically to Latinos have done well. Past programs rewarded customers who reached a set purchase limit with phone cards or PIN numbers. Food Lion cited in-store sampling as an effective tool as well.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBy taking the time to truly understand the audience you want to target, like Food Lion did with their custom programs, you will have greater success with your marketing programs.&nbsp; Everyone knows that a one size fits all approach does not work well &ndash; especially in marketing, so go beyond the surface level and dive deep into the many campaign targeting and data sources available today.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you for visiting the OnPoint Blog! If you have any questions, comments or inquiries, please contact <a href="mailto:onpoint@maxpointinteractive.com">onpoint@maxpoint.com</a>.</p>\r\n	t	2012-07-20 16:53:24	\N	2014-01-07 16:58:03.140209	2014-01-07 16:58:32.815547	49	\N
725	1	15	get-a-head-start-this-back-to-school-season-with-digital-advertising	Get a Head Start This Back-to-School Season with Digital Advertising 	<p>If you are ahead of the game, back-to-school planning begins early in the New Year, making sure advertising creative is perfected to the fullest. For the early birds, here are some things to keep in mind when planning back-to-school digital campaigns in 2012:</p>\r\n	<p>Back-to-school is a big business, with nearly $69B in sales at stake. That makes it the second-biggest selling season next to the winter holidays, as well as a huge marketing period for brands and retailers.&nbsp; However, unlike the holidays, retailers can rely on shoppers to head in-store for back-to-school because parents must purchase required school supplies or new school clothes &ndash; giving retailers a huge opportunity to focus on marketing to get shoppers to buy their brands. If you are ahead of the game, back-to-school planning begins early in the New Year, making sure advertising creative is perfected to the fullest. For the early birds, here are some things to keep in mind when planning back-to-school digital campaigns in 2012: <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Reach:</strong> This back-to-school season, precisely reach the right audience online who matches your back-to-school shopper profile with localized advertising. Targeted campaigns result in more engaging and relevant experiences for customers. By localizing digital advertising campaigns, ads can still have scale (reaching many consumers, not just a small group) at the local level, serving relevant ads to relevant consumers. According to MaxPoint&rsquo;s COO, Gretchen Joyce, &ldquo;whether you are rolling out an in-stream video campaign to a targeted audience or creating a digital coupon campaign that drives shoppers to purchase multiple products at a retail location &ndash; digital localization is one of the most cost-effective and impactful ways to drive in-store sales.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHear more on localized advertising from our COO <a href="http://staging.maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2012/2/22/what-is-the-state-of-localized-advertising-in-retail" target="_blank">here</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Leverage video:&nbsp;</strong> After pinpointing the right back-to-school audience, create a strong marketing mix that doesn&rsquo;t just leverage online display but leverages online video as well. Online video advertising has quickly become a highly engaging way for retailers and brands to reach their audiences. By targeting video ads at a local level, marketers can ensure that those consumers most interested in a product and most able to buy it see the ad. For instance, leverage your back-to-school TV spots and transform them into a video ad, reaching more people for a longer period of time and for less money.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRead more on online video advertising <a href="http://www.maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-solutions" target="_blank">here</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo get your creative juices flowing, look back at these <a href="http://adage.com/article/news/top-10-back-school-ads-tech-apparel/229485/">top back-to-school ads</a> from 2011.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Engage:&nbsp;</strong> Once you have strategized ways to target and reach shoppers, make sure your campaigns engage. For example, this back-to-school season, shoppers will head in-store but will be mindful of their budget. Try price-focused messaging to make consumers aware that you are looking out for them this shopping season. For example, J.C. Penney&rsquo;s &ldquo;Smart looks for less&rdquo; message is included on many of its advertisements to remind shoppers that they keep shoppers&rsquo; budgets in mind.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOther retailers and brands recognize that parents are not the only ones heading in-store for back-to-school but teens as well. J.C. Penney uses mobile to let teenage shoppers use a &ldquo;style mixer&rdquo; which helps them preview, mix and match outfits before making their final purchase. Others use celebrities in advertisements that really appeal to teenage consumer interests. The longer you keep shoppers engaged, the more likely your message is reinforced in their head and the more likely you are to drive in-store traffic.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHow will you bring your campaigns home this back-to-school season? Tweet us <a href="https://twitter.com/maxpoint_int" target="_blank">@maxpoint_int</a> with the hashtag #backtoschool and share with us!</p>\r\n	t	2012-02-20 15:48:50	\N	2012-02-20 15:48:50	2013-10-01 19:17:27.357359	51	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, digital, digital advertising, back-to-school, campaigns, campaign planning, retail, brands, retailers, reach, Gretchen Joyce, localization, video, online video advertising, engage, @maxpoint_int   
718	1	15	maxpoint-interactive-interest-index-tells-advertisers-that-miami-residents-are-most-intent-on-looking-and-acting-their-best-for-valentines-day	MaxPoint Interactive Interest Index Tells Advertisers that Miami Residents Are Most Intent on Looking and Acting Their Best for Valentine's Day 	<p>As Valentine&rsquo;s Day approaches, people start preparing to look their best for that special romantic night by getting the perfect haircut, shopping for that perfect outfit and buying the perfect red lipstick. Knowing the anticipation that builds around this holiday, we were interested in finding out what neighborhoods were most interested in looking and acting their best this Valentine&rsquo;s Day.</p>\r\n	<p>As Valentine&rsquo;s Day approaches, people start preparing to look their best for that special romantic night by getting the perfect haircut, shopping for that perfect outfit and buying the perfect red lipstick. Knowing the anticipation that builds around this holiday, we were interested in finding out what neighborhoods were most interested in looking and acting their best this Valentine&rsquo;s Day. <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis week we issued the results of our monthly indexing study that analyzed billions of data points to determine the U.S. neighborhoods most interested in looking and acting their best this Valentine&rsquo;s Day. Miami topped the list, which is scored based on consumer interest in topics such as beauty treatments, shopping for luxury fashion brands, cosmetics and dating advice.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition to Miami, FL, the cities that indexed the highest for people most interested in looking and acting their best for Valentine&rsquo;s Day are:<span id="cke_bm_338C" style="display:none">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Miami, FL</li>\r\n\t<li>Austin, TX</li>\r\n\t<li>Madison, WI</li>\r\n\t<li>Los Angeles, CA</li>\r\n\t<li>Norfolk, VA</li>\r\n\t<li>Omaha, NE</li>\r\n\t<li>Davenport, IA</li>\r\n\t<li>Fairbanks, AK</li>\r\n\t<li>Phoenix, AZ</li>\r\n\t<li>Baltimore, MD</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nUsing the data from this index, we were able to implement highly-targeted digital campaigns at the neighborhood level for a variety of retailers and brands. For example:<span id="cke_bm_337C" style="display:none">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Helped a high-end clothing retailer drive traffic of a discrete fashion conscious audience within an eight mile radius of their stores. By using MaxPoint&rsquo;s solution, the retailer was able to eliminate 89 percent of wasteful ad spend by targeting its key demographic at the neighborhood level.</li>\r\n\t<li>Increased awareness and sales of cosmetics for a major retailer at stores where beauty department sales were weak.</li>\r\n\t<li>Drove sales of a new acne treatment for a skincare company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAccording to our COO, Gretchen Joyce, &ldquo;Wasteful ad spending is a thing of the past. The results our customers have experienced be leveraging interest index information have proven that targeting consumers at the neighborhood level is not only a successful advertising strategy, but it&rsquo;s very impactful on the bottom line.&rdquo; Whether you are rolling out an in-stream video campaign to a targeted audience or creating a digital coupon campaign that drives shoppers to purchase multiple products at a retail location &ndash; digital localization is one of the most cost-effective and impactful ways to drive in-store sales.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo read the full release, click <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/online-advertising-news/valentines-day-interest" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n	t	2012-02-08 15:18:19	\N	2012-02-08 15:18:19	2013-10-01 19:51:15.019829	54	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, interest index, MaxPoint indexing study, indexing, targeting, campaigns, Valentine's Day, Miami, cities, neighborhoods, data, consumer interest, retail, brands, Gretchen Joyce, digital advertising   
867	1	20	5-tips-to-charge-your-mobile-campaigns	5 Tips to Charge Your Mobile Campaigns	<p>A recent study from eMarketer found that Americans now spend more time interacting with digital devices than they spend watching TV. This new shift in media consumption is largely due to growth in mobile activity.</p>\r\n	<p><img alt="Man on Mobile Phone" src="/system/editor/W1siZiIsIjIwMTMvMDgvMTUvMTBfNDBfMDVfMTg1X01hbl9vbl9Nb2JpbGVfMTUweDE1MC5wbmciXSxbInAiLCJ0aHVtYiIsIjgwMHg4MDA%2BIl1d/Man-on-Mobile_150x150.png" style="border-style:solid; border-width:0px; float:left; height:103px; margin:0px 10px; width:103px" />A recent study <a href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article/Digital-Set-Surpass-TV-Time-Spent-with-US-Media/1010096" target="_blank">from eMarketer</a> found that Americans now spend more time interacting with digital devices than they spend watching TV. This new shift in media consumption is largely due to growth in mobile activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite the surge in the mobile audience, mobile ad spending just hasn&rsquo;t kept pace with spending for other digital advertising. Perhaps the technology is too new, or organizational inertia ties up ad budgets with spending on traditional media.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, with such a large, engaged audience, brands can&rsquo;t afford to leave mobile out of their media plans. But just throwing money at it won&rsquo;t work either. So as mobile advertisers find their footing, we&rsquo;ve seen some clear best practices start to take shape based on our experience running a variety of mobile campaigns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are our key tips to using mobile effectively:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Take Advantage of the Full Mobile Experience&mdash;</strong>If you want to truly engage your customers, take advantage of all the capabilities mobile offers. For example, providing a click-to-call number puts the customer on the phone with a single finger tap&mdash;a small convenience that dramatically improves the customer experience. Of course, mobile technology goes beyond click-to-call to include QR codes, mobile coupons, mobile-responsive sites, and click-to map features. Mobile is about convenience, so keep that in mind with your advertising.<br />\r\n\t&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Look for the Right Placement Mix&mdash;</strong>General digital advertising provides options: different banner sizes, site placements, banner animations, pre-roll video, and more. Mobile also provides the ability to target on sites or within applications. MaxPoint finds in-app ads to be highly effective, but ultimately, you have to test for what works best for your campaigns.<br />\r\n\t&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Skip the Cookies&mdash;</strong>Customer reach via cookie-based targeting is small on desktop advertising&mdash;it&rsquo;s even smaller on mobile. <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2013/7/8/perhaps-cookies-might-not-be-so-sweet" target="_blank">We&rsquo;ve mentioned it before</a>, but browsers on most mobile devices (particularly Safari on the iPhone/iPad) do not accept third-party cookies by default. This means you&rsquo;ll need to find a way to target without relying on cookies to make a real impact.<br />\r\n\t&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Go Easy on Geofencing&mdash;</strong>Speaking of targeting, geofencing, which involves sending a targeted message to shoppers when they&rsquo;re located within an extremely tight radius, is currently popular among mobile advertisers. But as <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2013/5/3/mobile-geofencing-an-advertising-trap" target="_blank">we&rsquo;ve said before</a>, geofencing simply doesn&rsquo;t scale. Effective hyperlocal advertising delivers the power of local precision while still casting a wide-enough net to give your campaign the scale that matters.<br />\r\n\t&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Keep Your Message Consistent&mdash;</strong>It&rsquo;s always important to reinforce your brand across channels, but it&rsquo;s critical when you throw mobile into the mix. Consumers frequently use their mobile devices, particularly tablets, while also watching TV or listening to the radio. Your mobile ad should support and enhance your other spots since customers are likely to be exposed to both messages at the same time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMobile may be the new kid on the advertising block, but you shouldn&rsquo;t wait to get on the bandwagon. And even if you&rsquo;re already on, consider spending even more of your budget on this engaged audience.</p>\r\n	t	2013-08-14 13:23:27	\N	2013-08-14 13:28:01.026008	2013-09-04 16:52:10.570314	59	\N
722	1	26	did-you-get-the-most-out-of-your-super-bowl-ad	Did You Get the Most Out of Your Super Bowl Ad?	<p>Super Bowl ads definitely get attention.&nbsp; It&#39;s no wonder, then, why advertisers paid upwards of $3.5MM for a 30-second spot during Super Bowl XLVI this year.</p>\r\n	<p>By now, you have already seen the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0-9EYFJ4Clo" target="_blank">Volkswagen</a> one with the weight-conscious dog and Star Wars theme (The Dog Strikes Back!).&nbsp; Everyone&#39;s been talking about the sexy <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yn3mktl30iw&amp;list=UUWStqpgu1Pt3VhXCOGlmkkw&amp;feature=plcp" target="_blank">M&amp;M</a>!&nbsp; Oh, and two words:&nbsp; <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uWrJgFjxlS0" target="_blank">Adriana Lima</a>.&nbsp; Super Bowl ads definitely get attention.&nbsp; It&#39;s no wonder, then, why advertisers paid upwards of $3.5MM for a 30-second spot during Super Bowl XLVI this year.<!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis may seem like a lot of money, but when you consider the sheer number of households tuning in to the Super Bowl each year, some actually find it cheap.&nbsp; In the <a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2012/02/super-bowl-ads-are-cheap-35-million-for-30-seconds-isnt-enough/252591/" target="_blank">Atlantic</a> this week, <a href="https://twitter.com/DKThomp" target="_blank">@dkthomp</a> writes that, &quot;When it comes to targeted advertising, the Super Bowl is in a league of its own. The top two television events in history were the last two Super Bowl games, with the last one netting 111 million watchers.&quot;&nbsp; Add in the fact that entire groups of people are gathered together in front of a TV, attentions glued on the screen during commercial breaks, specifically for the ads!&nbsp; Taking all this into account, $3.5MM for a Super Bowl ad is a steal!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHowever, while a Super Bowl spot will certainly buy you a wide audience, are you actually hitting the right target?&nbsp; $3.5MM may be a small price to pay in terms of reaching the most Americans, but does it pay off when it comes to efficiently reaching the specific audience for your product?&nbsp; While Budweiser may have hit their beer-guzzling 21+ male audience, did <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y59VUQxX3Dk" target="_blank">Oikos Yogurt</a> or David Beckham for <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eQb_-OY7Z0E" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a> reach theirs?<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUltimately, what makes an ad effective is not just creating talk, but driving sales. And, what we know here at MaxPoint is that, <strong>when it comes to targeted advertising, going local is what works</strong>.&nbsp; For a high-end greek yogurt brand, we can find those households within an 8-mile radius of a grocery retailer for your brand.&nbsp; From there, we overlay additional targeting to only display ads to those neighborhoods that index highly for women 25-54, who are college-educated, middle- to upper-class, and interested in a health conscious lifestyle.&nbsp; For a fashionable clothing retailer, we can target ads specifically to neighborhoods that over-index for young men, around your retail locations.&nbsp; We have seen from numerous digital campaigns that these tactics are effective in driving traffic to your local grocery chain or retailer, resulting in real sales - not just talk.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAny advertiser can take advantage of our technology by running pre-roll video, in-banner video display, or standard flash and rich media display ads.&nbsp; Even better, prolong the life of your ad and Super Bowl conversation by pairing a TV spot with a digital campaign, utilizing MaxPoint&#39;s neighborhood-targeted local solution.&nbsp; Ads made for TV can be easily converted to a pre-roll video ad or in-banner video ad, and MaxPoint&#39;s targeting would deliver the ads only to the audience you care most about reaching.&nbsp; Reinforce your TV message, drive in-store sales, and eliminate waste, all at a fraction of the price!&nbsp; Now how&#39;s that for a steal?</p>\r\n	t	2012-02-15 14:55:18	\N	2012-02-15 14:55:18	2013-10-01 19:34:41.437633	51	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, Dannon, Jenny Bo, Super Bowl, Super Bowl campaigns, campaigns, advertising, online, digital advertising, Volkswagen, H&M, Atlantic, targeting, targeted advertising, local, digital, video
721	1	15	doing-business-in-bentonville-event-recap-in-store-impact-of-merchandising-within-walmart	Doing Business in Bentonville Event Recap: In-store Impact of Merchandising within Walmart 	<p>Last week, MaxPoint headed to Arkansas for the first Doing Business in Bentonville event of the year to learn a little more on the in-store impact of merchandising within Walmart.</p>\r\n	<p>Last week, MaxPoint headed to Arkansas for the first Doing Business in Bentonville event of the year to learn a little more on the in-store impact of merchandising within <a href="http://www.walmart.com/" target="_blank">Walmart</a>. <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe retail industry (especially in Bentonville) is constantly evolving, and to keep up with what&rsquo;s most relevant today, it&rsquo;s important for industry leaders to continually seek out the best practices to improve business and decision making. Doing Business in Bentonville (DBB) is a professional speaking series for current and prospective suppliers to Walmart and <a href="http://www.samsclub.com/sams/" target="_blank">Sam&rsquo;s Club</a> stores that discuss this evolving retail industry and focus on best practices that are critical to success. Led by Nancy Woods, DBB develops and tailors programs to help attendees reach their full potential as a supplier to the world&rsquo;s largest retailer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAt this first event, attendees heard from SVP of Merchandising at Walmart on the in-store impact of merchandising within Walmart. The speaker addressed how you can correctly merchandise a product within Walmart, such as setting up displays and how to market along Walmart guidelines.&nbsp; In addition, the speaker briefly touched on how to drive in-store traffic to Walmart.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDid you miss the event but are interested in learning more on driving in-store traffic in general? Subscribe to our <a href="http://www.maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog" target="_blank">OnPoint blog</