883	1	37	upgrade-your-digital-advertising-with-pixels	Upgrade Your Digital Advertising with Pixels	<p>Find out how to use real-time data to get audience intelligence that can improve your campaigns even more.</p>\r\n	<p>I&rsquo;m clueless about cars. I rarely look under the hood, can&rsquo;t change my own oil, and am only vaguely aware that I have a spare tire in the trunk. I would rather leave everything to professional mechanics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Real-Time Insights" src="/system/editor/W1siZiIsIjIwMTMvMTAvMDkvMTRfMDRfMDdfNTA2X1N0b3B3YXRjaF8yMDB4MjAwLnBuZyJdLFsicCIsInRodW1iIiwiODAweDgwMD4iXV0/Stopwatch_200x200.png" style="float:right; height:180px; width:180px" />But with digital advertising, you really should pop the hood to see what&rsquo;s powering your campaigns. For example, many advertisers rely on third-party cookies for their targeting. We&rsquo;ve covered <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2013/7/8/perhaps-cookies-might-not-be-so-sweet" target="_blank">the limitations of cookies before</a>, but we didn&rsquo;t mention that most purchased cookies are 90 days old by the time they&rsquo;re used. In Internet Standard Time, that&rsquo;s an eternity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One way to get fresher data is to use audience intelligence pixels. They provide real-time behavioral insights that you can use to drive your hyperlocal advertising response even higher.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let me give you an example. Let&rsquo;s say you&rsquo;re pushing new shoppers to request samples for a cologne. You target your usual demographic, which is single men making over $60,000 per year. But you need to target a subset of shoppers within that demographic to find men most likely to request samples. To find them, your digital provider can place pixels on your home page and several internal pages to find the highest converting group among your organic and paid web traffic. You might discover that men in the suburbs tend to request samples online, while urbanites stick to sampling in-store. This makes it a no-brainer: target men who live in the suburbs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, this can go a step further. Imagine that, two weeks into the campaign, a famous quarterback mentions your brand of cologne as his personal fragrance. You will likely see sales spike in neighborhoods packed with his fans. If you&rsquo;ve pixeled the right pages, you&rsquo;ll note the traffic spike and can strike while the iron is hot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The bottom line is that pixels provide audience intelligence in real time in ways that third-party cookies alone simply can&rsquo;t. Adding the data available from pixels into an overall audience intelligence model will upgrade the engines currently running your digital campaigns.</p>\r\n	t	2013-10-09 19:01:57	\N	2013-10-09 19:03:55.234915	2013-10-09 19:04:43.482373	52	\N
834	1	15	interest-index-reveals-top-cities-with-sports-fans-and-exercise-enthusiasts	Top Cities with Sports Fans and Exercise Enthusiasts	<p>Are you more of a sports fan or physical fitness buff? We wanted to find out so we issued the results today of an indexing study that reveals the neighborhoods across the country with sports fans and exercise enthusiasts.</p>\r\n	<p>Are you more of a sports fan or physical fitness buff? We wanted to find out so we issued the results today of an indexing study that reveals the neighborhoods across the country with sports fans and exercise enthusiasts. <!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter analyzing billions of offline and online we found that neighborhoods in the Washington, DC, area have the highest concentration of people interested in athletics.&nbsp; The Index data further revealed that there are two unique personas when it comes to staying active: those who enjoy watching and supporting organized sports teams, and those who enjoy working on their own physical fitness.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Potomac Hills neighborhood in McLean, Virginia, indexed highest for its interest in sports teams, while the Garfield Heights neighborhood in the District of Columbia prefers to focus on personal exercise routines. This information is extremely valuable to advertisers who offer products or services that appeal to either sports fans or exercise enthusiasts but not necessarily both groups.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>The top 10 cities that show the greatest interest in athletics are:</strong><br />\r\n1. Washington, DC<br />\r\n2. Binghamton, NY<br />\r\n3. Santa Barbara, CA<br />\r\n4. Minneapolis, MN<br />\r\n5. Gainesville, FL<br />\r\n6. Philadelphia, PA<br />\r\n7. Honolulu, HI<br />\r\n8. Madison, WI<br />\r\n9. St. Louis, MO<br />\r\n10. Denver, CO<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUsing the data gleaned from the September Interest Index, we implemented hyperlocal digital advertising campaigns geared toward sports fans and fitness enthusiasts:<span id="cke_bm_99C" style="display:none">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>A CPG manufacturer of a new line of energy-enhancing cereal wanted to reach men who had both an interest in sports and an active lifestyle. We implemented an ad campaign featuring professional male athletes that targeted those men who met the shopper profile and who lived within a certain radius of a big-box store carrying the cereal.</li>\r\n\t<li>A regional yoga studio wanted to increase membership at two of its Manhattan locations. We executed a hyperlocal digital ad campaign targeting New York City neighborhoods that over-indexed for an interest in fitness. The campaign targeted only those neighborhoods within a certain radius of each studio that had residents with an income of more than $100,000.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&ldquo;Interest in athletes, teams and athletic events is hugely popular among consumers today, which is very appealing to advertisers who look to capitalize on this growing market to sell their product or service,&rdquo; said Gretchen Joyce, chief operating officer at MaxPoint Interactive. &ldquo;Yet, the challenge for advertisers is that this interest varies across such a wide spectrum of sports, teams and exercise types that it is often difficult to reach the right audience. MaxPoint helps these advertisers pinpoint a very specific audience at the neighborhood level and use that information to create a highly effective digital advertising campaign that drives in-store traffic.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/advertising-tips-and-strategies/advertising-insights/sports-and-exercise-interest"><img alt="" class="alignleft size-large wp-image-3314" src="http://maxpointinteractive.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/MaxPoint-Interactive-September-2012-Interest-Index-Infographic-297x1024.png" style="height:1024px; width:297px" title="MaxPoint-Interactive-September-2012-Interest-Index-Infographic" /></a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo check out last month&rsquo;s Interest Index report, <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/advertising-tips-and-strategies/advertising-insights/back-to-school-lunches" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p>\r\n	t	2012-09-27 13:56:24	\N	2012-09-27 13:56:24	2013-09-10 16:59:49.369932	54	Digital Zip, interest index, MaxPoint, neighborhoods, fitness, sports
