866	1	37	4-reasons-to-use-digital-for-your-branding-campaigns	More Than Sales: 4 Reasons to Use Digital for Your Branding Campaigns	<p>Digital advertising is becoming the weapon of choice for advertisers and brands looking to build their sales. With good reason&mdash;digital advertising boosts traffic to websites and to stores. But digital is also a powerful branding tool.</p>\r\n	<p>Digital advertising is becoming the weapon of choice for advertisers and brands looking to build their sales. With good reason&mdash;digital advertising boosts traffic to websites and to stores. But digital is also a powerful branding tool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facing dwindling print readership and declining TV viewership, advertisers are increasingly placing their branding budgets in digital channels. This goes beyond digital display ads&mdash;advertisers are seeing excellent results from mobile display and digital video as well. In other words, they&rsquo;re learning the power of digital to promote the right messages to the right markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The odds are good that you already devote some of your media plan to digital. However, you may want to shift a bigger share online. Here are just four key reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Reach a large audience.</strong> The key to a successful awareness campaign is to cast a wide net&mdash;and digital delivers. And it&rsquo;s not just younger audiences that spend their time online&mdash;a <a href="http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/205122/#axzz2ae5VM67s" target="_blank">recent MediaPost article</a> claims that 60% of baby boomers say, &ldquo;watching online video an important part of their day.&rdquo;<a href="#_ftn1" name="_ftnref1" title="">[1]</a> People in nearly every age bracket continue to adopt digital as a key media source. As a result, the digital audience grows day by day.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Advertise cost-effectively. </strong>In addition to its scale, digital brings cost effectiveness to the table. Compared to traditional advertising, you can spend your budget far more efficiently online. For example, every dollar spent with MaxPoint allows an advertiser to reach triple the number of markets than with traditional DMA targeting.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Reduce wasted impressions.</strong> For print advertising, you don&rsquo;t just pay to reach your customers&mdash;you pay to reach people outside of your demographic. For every newspaper reader who fits your audience segment, there are several who don&rsquo;t. Digital targeting decreases wasted impressions by focusing on a cross segment of a website&rsquo;s visitors. If you really want your brand message to sink in with the ideal audience, then digital is the way to go.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Measure brand lift more easily. </strong>To measure a brand advertisement&rsquo;s effectiveness, you often have to run focus groups that are both expensive and time consuming. But with digital, you can get an accurate brand lift result simply by running a survey in place of an ad impression. For example, if you&rsquo;re running a branding campaign that promotes a cereal as &ldquo;heart-healthy,&rdquo; then you can run a single-question survey to customers that asks if they perceive the cereal is helpful for reducing blood pressure. This provides quick results in a fraction of the time of a focus group.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nIf you really want to get the biggest bang for your digital buck, then you have to go hyperlocal. And if you use MaxPoint, hyperlocal precision comes without the loss of scale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, let&rsquo;s say that an advertising company that sells bedding needs to boost sales of its hypoallergenic bedding line in the Portland, OR market. A digital campaign could help position the company as the leading brand of hypoallergenic bedding within the market. To accomplish this, they should target households with interests in allergy relief that are located around stores that carry the bedding. As a result, they can deliver an effective, focused message to a perfectly focused crowd.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to advertising campaigns, you simply can&rsquo;t get a more versatile and effective channel than digital advertising. The tendency online is to focus on sales and responses&mdash;but don&rsquo;t discount the power of digital branding. And if you want to build extremely targeted awareness in a focused market or audience segment, then go the extra step with a hyperlocal digital advertising campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="#_ftnref1" name="_ftn1" title="">[1]</a> <a href="http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/205122/#axzz2ae5VM67s" target="_blank">http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/205122/#axzz2ae5VM67s</a></p>\r\n	t	2013-08-05 13:36:06	\N	2013-08-05 13:42:16.540208	2013-09-04 14:49:53.542624	48	\N
