700	1	15	retailers-our-top-ten-ways-to-bring-shoppers-holiday-cheer	Retailers: Our Top Ten Ways to Bring Shoppers Holiday Cheer	<p>For many shoppers heading to the mall around the holidays is not an easy feat.&nbsp; Breaking a sweat just trying to get through the parking lot, the task does not get any easier with crazy store crowds and battles over toys once in-store. So&hellip;retailers, what can you do for these brave shoppers? Make the holiday in-store shopping experience as pleasant as possible.</p>\r\n	<p>For many shoppers heading to the mall around the holidays is not an easy feat.&nbsp; Breaking a sweat just trying to get through the parking lot, the task does not get any easier with crazy store crowds and battles over toys once in-store. However, this hustle and bustle is expected around this time of year and as consumers, we&rsquo;ve accepted it, continuing to head in-store every holiday season. So&hellip;retailers, what can you do for these brave shoppers? Make the holiday in-store shopping experience as pleasant as possible. Below are ten ways you can bring shoppers holiday cheer this year. <!--more--></p>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Be kid-friendly!</strong> Make the lives of shoppers who bring their children in-store a little easier by providing a kid-friendly environment. Offer an in-store day-care service and give parents an hour away to shop, hands-free. Not equipped for a day-care service? Try providing kid-friendly carts for parents with children or pass out treats or toys to keep kids occupied.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Make use of digital displays.</strong> Entertain and engage in-store shoppers with digital displays. For example, <a href="http://www.macys.com/?cm_mmc=GOOGLE_Trademark-_-Macys+Trademark+Exact+-+G_Macy%27s-_-7652215760_Exact-_-macys._mkwid_sD8ZWkSIK_7652215760|-|D8ZWkSIK" target="_blank">Macy&rsquo;s</a> Believe Stations use digital elements to give shoppers one unique and entertaining holiday experience. More <a href="http://www.marketwatch.com/story/macys-introduces-augmented-reality-experience-in-stores-across-country-as-part-of-its-2011-believe-campaign-2011-11-02" target="_blank">here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Provide coat/bag checks.</strong> Most shoppers will be hitting multiple stores at once, which means lugging around heavy bags in addition to outdoor winter gear. Provide shoppers with coat/bag checks and let them shop around in your store with ease. Free arms = more hands to pull items off shelves, into the cart and onto check-out.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Give out samples.</strong> Make purchase decisions faster by offering samples of your products. Sell food and beverage items? Pass around trays with food and beverage samples. Not only will it ease hunger pains during shopping (eliminating the desire to leave the store for food) but allow shoppers to walk away knowing they purchased exactly what they wanted. Sell games?&nbsp; Provide a station where shoppers can play the latest games and even compete against other shoppers for bragging rights or the rights to that toy they might be fighting over.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Be equipped with full staff/extra cashiers</strong>.&nbsp; A full staff is key during the holiday shopping season. Multiple hands can help multiple shoppers, eliminating crowds faster and pleasing shoppers by making it easy to find and have a store representative ready to answer questions. Also, remember to open up all possible checkout lines and even find ways to provide additional ways to checkout. Consumers accept it, but the last thing they want to do during the holidays is wait in lines. For alternative checkout options, see this <a href="http://www.retailtouchpoints.com/resource-center/51-white-papers/1194-enabling-smarter-commerce-mobile-point-of-sale-and-mobile-commerce-stores" target="_blank">article</a> on mobile checkout.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Offer free wrapping.</strong> Trying to find the right present for everyone in the family is hard enough and unless you are a super pro at wrapping, many struggle and do not look forward to this daunting task. Bring a smile to shoppers&rsquo; faces as they notice free wrapping stations after checking out. Now, that&rsquo;s a line worth waiting in.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Put up store directories.</strong> Larger stores, department stores in particular, can be hard to navigate. Provide shoppers with store directories so they can get to where they are going faster. And, make it festive too! Provide arrows to the hottest holiday items or use holiday icons for &ldquo;you are here&rdquo; markers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Strategically organize popular items.</strong> As we&rsquo;ve touched on again and again, crowds are common during the holiday shopping season. Strategically place popular items far enough away from each other to avoid creating mob-like mentality in one area of the store.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Offer incentives for coming in-store.</strong> Let shoppers know you appreciate them coming in-store by offering incentives. For instance, use social networks like <a href="https://foursquare.com/" target="_blank">Foursquare</a> to let shoppers gain points towards a store reward every time they check-in in-store. Or&hellip;offer discounts only available in-store. Either way, shoppers will be happy you are thinking of them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul><br />\r\n\t<li><strong>Be merry!</strong> Good customer service is key to pleasing shoppers, especially during the holiday shopping rush. Unhappy employees = unhappy shoppers. So listen to that holiday music loud on the way to work and get ready to spread cheer to everyone in-store. Read more about customer service and its role in marketing <a href="http://adage.com/article/news/customer-service-playing-bigger-role-marketing-tool/230838/" target="_blank">here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nWe wish everyone a happy and safe 2011 holiday shopping season!</p>\r\n	t	2011-12-21 15:32:40	\N	2011-12-21 15:32:40	2013-10-02 23:40:14.604623	49	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, Retail TouchPoints, holiday shopping tips, retail, holiday, 2011, holiday shopping, holiday shopping season, Macy's, Macy's Believe Stations, tips, top ten, in-store, shoppers, MarketWatch, Advertising Age 
