o;Coke wants to show commitment to make the world a better place.&rdquo; To inspire consumers to live positively, each advertisement is aimed to leave viewers with a happy and inspired mood after watching.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Listen to your customers:</strong> In order to drive brand sales, it is important to listen to consumers and discover their needs in order to deliver the best brand experience. However, according to Coca-Cola, listening to a consumer is not enough. A brand has to be actively involved in conversation and responding to consumers&rsquo; needs. One way to do this is by leveraging digital and building an online presence.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWatch Coca-Cola&rsquo;s viral videos <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/the-18-best-coke-youtube-videos-2012-6#the-hug-machine-1" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n	t	2012-06-21 15:03:49	\N	2012-06-21 15:03:49	2013-09-20 00:16:59.475581	49	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, digital, digital advertising, viral, brand
790	1	15	interactive-marketing-whats-in-store-for-the-future	Interactive Marketing, What is In Store for the Future	<p>Digital advertising now represents over 15 percent of all advertising spend and continues to become an integral part of most advertising plans. In fact, digital is the number one way to reach a broad (and highly demanded) demographic: 18-54 year olds. We have arrived at the &ldquo;digital decade&rdquo; and advertisers are now finding new ways to leverage this channel.</p>\r\n	<p>Digital advertising now represents over 15 percent of all advertising spend and continues to become an integral part of most advertising plans. In fact, digital is the number one way to reach a broad (and highly demanded) demographic: 18-54 year olds. We have arrived at the &ldquo;digital decade&rdquo; and advertisers are now finding new ways to leverage this channel.<!--more--><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are a few things advertisers and brands should keep in mind when using online advertising. From scale and reach, to cost-effectiveness, to speed and flexibility, digital enables advertisers to accomplish goals traditional ad routes cannot.&nbsp; And, in order to leverage online advertising to its fullest, advertisers will need to know how interactive marketing is changing marketing strategies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a recent Forrester Research research report, &ldquo;The Future of Interactive Marketing,&rdquo; Shar VanBoskirk, Research Vice President and lead analyst wrote, &ldquo;The next digital decade challenges the model of interactive marketing that most organizations have developed.&rdquo; As digital provides us with vast new opportunities for advertising, marketers need to re-think their traditional strategy. Here are a few ways interactive marketing will change advertising:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Focus on customer relationships:</strong> Digital vehicles and interactive tools give us much more of an opportunity to communicate and engage with consumers. For instance, social media networking sites give insight into what consumers are talking about and sharing. It is also a great place for retailers/brands to reach out to consumers directly. In addition, audience targeting technologies enable advertisers and brands to reach consumers online at a very granular level, making sure the right consumer sees an advertisement that is relevant to them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Remain open to new technology:</strong> U.S. online advertising is predicted to jump from $39.5 billion in 2012 to $62 billion in 2016. And, as online advertising grows, there will be even more technologies introduced to the market, more consumer insights available and more ways to reach consumers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Penetrate all media:</strong> According to VanBoskirk, &ldquo;Interactivity is penetrating traditional media and advertising&hellip;Along with changes in media come changes in media buying.&rdquo; Media buyers and planners will have to evaluate the most efficient methods for running a campaign with multiple outlets available. In addition, more media buyers and planners are starting to allocate more ad spend on budgets for digital, while others are learning how to create and optimize cross-channel campaigns. Read more on creating cross-channel campaigns <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2012/5/9/creating-cross-platform-campaigns-what-works-what-to-avoid" target="_blank">here</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo read more on the growth of online advertising, click <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2012/6/18/online-ad-revenue-whats-behind-the-growth" target="_blank">here</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo check out infographics that capture the growth of online advertising, click <a href="http://maxpoint.com/us/digital-advertising-company/onpoint-blog/2012/6/15/online-ad-spending-infographic" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n	t	2012-06-20 13:59:51	\N	2012-06-20 13:59:51	2013-09-20 00:23:51.036881	49	MaxPoint, MaxPoint Interactive, OnPoint, interactive marketing, online advertising, digital, digital decade
