876	1	44	real-time-advertising-the-perfect-ads-at-the-perfect-time	Real-Time Advertising: The Perfect Ads at the Perfect Time	<p>Want to boost your responses and lower your ad waste? Try real-time advertising&mdash;it&#39;s easier than you think.</p>\r\n	<p><img alt="Coffee" src="/system/editor/W1siZiIsIjIwMTMvMDkvMjUvMTNfNDhfMDZfODAxX0NvZmZlZS5qcGciXSxbInAiLCJ0aHVtYiIsIjgwMHg4MDA%2BIl1d/Coffee.jpg" style="float:right; height:200px; margin:10px 5px; width:300px" /> The most powerful advertisements share one major commonality&mdash;relevance. They speak to your world in the most relevant way possible. When you&rsquo;re hungry, an ad for a burger might be perfect. When you&rsquo;re thirsty, bottled water might do the trick. The closer an ad speaks to your current experience, the more likely it is you&rsquo;ll buy the product. And digital advertising helps you do this better than any other advertising channel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over the past year, real-time ads have been the talk of the advertising town. And for good reason&mdash;they make use of digital&rsquo;s full potential by making ads far more timely and relevant. Whether you&rsquo;re watching the Oscars or the Indy 500, you feel like the ad is right next to you enjoying the same event. You simply can&rsquo;t do this with print advertising.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But while real-time advertising sounds complicated, it can be a lot easier than you think. It just takes the right creative and a little extra planning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, let&rsquo;s say you run a coffee shop. You could serve ads promoting a cold iced drink when the weather is warm, but promote a warm latte once the temperature drops below freezing. Your creative can even reference the weather: &ldquo;Warm up from the cold with a nice warm latte.&rdquo; The customer is likely already thinking about the weather, so your ads offer her the perfect suggestion for the temperature. When it&rsquo;s cold, it&rsquo;s only logical that you&rsquo;d like to warm up with a nice cup of coffee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weather-based ads aren&rsquo;t the only application for real-time ads. For example, let&rsquo;s say you&rsquo;re a shoe brand. If there&rsquo;s a major fashion show on TV, you can try to serve ads promoting your brand of shoe to customers in areas watching the fashion show. Your customers could receive ads on their smartphones or tablets that promote the shoes right as the model strolls down the catwalk wearing your brand. It&rsquo;s a real-time ad that didn&rsquo;t require any scrambling from a creative agency or the executive team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ultimately, advertising is about relevance&mdash;the right location at the right time. Hyperlocal digital advertising already gives you the location piece; now, real-time ads give you time-relevance. And you don&rsquo;t need luck&mdash;with a little bit of planning and the right data, you can serve your ads to customers right when they&rsquo;re perfectly poised to hear them. Digital advertising gives you the flexibility to adapt to changing conditions in the world&mdash;whether you have to swap out creative or simply increase your ad buys in a specific area. By being highly relevant, you improve your response rates while reducing your ad waste. And that&rsquo;s the dream of every advertiser, isn&rsquo;t it?</p>\r\n	t	2013-09-20 13:54:41	\N	2013-09-20 13:59:56.634917	2013-10-01 18:07:22.222639	63	\N
